Does anyone else here grow? I'm finishing up my first run, and I don't think I'll ever plant regular seeds again lol. Took a lot of time to weed out the males, and my autoflowers were done in 1/2 the time. My next run will be autos and fems, feel free to follow my journey! https://www.instagram.com/stoneyjabroni510/
dont grow but def keep letting us know how it goes
would love to hear

about $500-800 per tent setup (tent, light(s), fans, filter, timer) and about $10-20/mo on electricity, water,  and nutrients. Would definitely recommend for anyone looking to start a new hobby! My first autoflowers were ready to smoke 111days from planting 👍
how much yield did you get
in 3x 1gal pots, I had about 1/2 o per plant. so about 1.5oz in 111days lol. I'd definitely recommend using pots bigger than 1gal. this next run I'll be growing my autos in 5gal pots

definitely haven't broke-even yet; but I'd value this 1.5o around $160ish. the quality was better than I expected for a first grow. hoping to be getting at least 2 o's per plant soon, then upping it to 3-4oz/plant once I get the technique dialed in. (low stress training & nutrients) ~ also it's tons of fun to have a year-round growing season. I'll be hanging out with my buds all winter
interesting!
any beginning resources you used
blogs, videos, etc
@somehippie

Mr. Canucks ~ the autoflower+ Rosin-press king, known for using dry fertilizers. If you're in Canada and have access to gaia green dry fertilizers this would be really easy to follow. Although choosing your nutrient line is very opinionated, he uses Dutch Passion seeds, which is a well known breeder from Amsterdam https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1a3jEPge-QE

Dutch Passion ~ they have a great blog, and their website has tons of info on each of their strains. These breeders were the first to feminize seeds, and are well known in Amsterdam https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bOAgWenmZp0

Weed in a Pot ~ this guy makes easy to follow videos, just talking about the science of weed. I usually use his videos to start before choosing my own methods https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCCMM7iUIUx7Yu8B_uOiF3wA

DrMjCoco ~ university teacher who really understands LED lighting. His website has a calculator to figure out your best Light/Tent setup (spoiler, the Mars Hydro SP3000 is currently the best light under $400, followed by the Spiderfarmer SF1000 at $160, which has less than half the output but did really good for my first grow. Keep an eye out for the Samsung LM301b and LM301H diodes) https://youtu.be/ztBHfvNe1OY

Seedsman has a huge list of breeders and ships worldwide. It takes just over a month to get your order in, but it allows me to order from breeders such as Dutch Passion or Greenhouse Seed Co (the ones from the Vice/HBO show Stain Hunters) https://www.seedsman.com/en/cannabis-seed-breeders
very helpful thank you man
Just bought some seeds planning to start growing when they arrive next month -- thanks for these resources will have some notes to compare @somehippie

FoxFarm's Ocean Forest is a great soil to start with if it's available in your area! https://foxfarm.com/product/ocean-forest-potting-soil
I start my seeds directly in this soil w/o any other additives. Some people mix their Ocean Forest with wormcastings, perlite, and/or Happy Frog Soil but I kept mine 100% Ocean Forest for my first run. I also planted 6 autoflowers directly in 5gal pots of this soil just 3 days ago! I'll post daily on the stoneyjabroni510 insta, but maybe I'll post some updates here if I download discord on my phone.
I'm currently using Neptune's Harvest Red (Veg) & Purple (Flower) as my main nutrients, but I'll probably experiment with other brands soon enough. to be a heretic and tldr on tim ferriss' opinion even more (focusing mainly on psychedelics): 
- They can be equally beneficial or destructive.  They have a potential since they open a window for your brain to become plastic and rewire your mind.

- Set and setting is everything. There are no bad trips, just unsafe trips.
- Drugs are not a mountain to conquer. Finding a tool which is sufficient for you - such as a holotropic breathwork session could be sufficient, no need to do 5-MeO-DMT. Start small and stop when you are helped.
